      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Up to 2500 m rain will fall in the next few hours. <br/> Wednesday: Some rain will fall from midday. <br/> In the last few days the weather was mild. This situation gave rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack below approximately 2800 m. <br/> As a consequence of highly fluctuating temperatures the snowpack consolidated. This applies in particular on steep sunny slopes at high altitude, and in all aspects at intermediate altitudes. <br/> Hardly any more avalanches were reported. <br/> The amount of snow is subject to significant local variations. <br/> Especially on sunny slopes below approximately 2600 m no snow is lying. On shady slopes below the tree line hardly any snow is lying. <br/> Weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack in particular in high Alpine regions."
      },
